FBIS4-34329 "drlat118_a_94020" FBIS-LAT-94-118 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Steel Industry, Slovak Firm Build Mopeds for Tourism Steel Industry, Slovak Firm Build Mopeds for Tourism FL1706113294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 16 Jun 94 FL1706113294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [From the "Exclusive" program] [Text] The Cuban steel industry has been assembling mopeds since April, in cooperation with Slovakia's (Howritz) firm. The national news agency reports that the mopeds will be earmarked for exportation and tourism and will eventually be assigned to state organizations. A total of 450 mopeds have been assembled to date. These mopeds can reach a maximum speed of between 40 and 50 km per hour.
